# Porting the dev-team to this project

This dev-team (`.claude/agents/`) is portable. The agents themselves contain
no project-specific identifiers — every GitHub Project ID, owner/repo name,
and skills path is read from `.claude/project.env` (sourced automatically by
`.claude/env.sh`).

If you're seeing this file, `init-project.sh` already created the scaffolding.
Work through this checklist top-to-bottom to finish wiring the team to your
GitHub project board. **Items marked _MANUAL_ require human action; the
agents cannot do them.**

---

## 1. What's already in place

`init-project.sh` has created (skipping anything that already existed):

```
.claude/
├── agents/                # the dev-team — do not edit
├── commands/              # /execute slash command
├── env.sh                 # toolchain bootstrap; auto-sources project.env,
│                          # derives TRACKER_BACKEND from CLAUDE.md, and
│                          # sources lib/tracker/tracker.sh
├── lib/tracker/           # tracker abstraction (dispatcher + 3 backends)
├── project.env            # ← per-project: edit this (step 4)
├── PORTING.md             # this file
├── copilot-instructions.md
├── settings.local.json    # local-only — gitignore it
└── templates/
CLAUDE.md                  # ← per-project: edit this (step 3)
_docs/
tracker/
```

---

## 2. Prerequisites _MANUAL_

Before the team can run, the host machine must have:

- [ ] **Python toolchain available**: `python` / `python3` / `py` on PATH (or installed at one of the locations probed by `env.sh:_find_python`)
- [ ] **`pytest`, `ruff`, `black`, `isort` installed** in that interpreter (verifiable via `source .claude/env.sh && check_toolchain`)
- [ ] **Superpowers skills present** at the path declared by `${SUPERPOWERS_SKILLS_DIR}` in `project.env` — each subdirectory should contain a `SKILL.md`
- [ ] **`jq` installed** — used by every `gh project item-list … | jq …` pipeline and by the Azure backend's WIQL parsing
- [ ] **`bats-core` installed** _(only if you want to run the tracker test suite — `make test-tracker`)_: `npm install -g bats`

Then, depending on the `tracker:` mode set in `CLAUDE.md`:

- For `tracker: github-issues`:
  - [ ] **`gh` CLI authenticated**: `gh auth status` returns OK
- For `tracker: azure-boards`:
  - [ ] **`az` CLI authenticated**: `az account show` returns OK
  - [ ] **`azure-devops` extension installed**: `az extension add --name azure-devops`
  - [ ] **PAT scope (if running headless / CI)**: `AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT` exported with at least *Work Items: Read & Write* and *Code: Read* scopes. Interactive workstations can rely on `az login` instead.

