## 6. Quick smoke test (optional)

Create a trivial issue on the new repo:

```bash
gh issue create --repo "${GH_OWNER}/${GH_REPO}" \
  --title "[SMOKE] Hello world" \
  --body "Smoke test for the dev-team setup." \
  --label "needs-grooming,priority-low,role-pm"
```

Then in Claude Code, run `/execute` (or invoke the `product-manager` agent
on that issue) and confirm:

- The PM agent grooms it without errors
- The label transitions to `ready-for-dev,role-swe`
- The project board's Pipeline column moves the item to **Development**

If both transitions work, the team is fully portable on this host.

